---
import Layout from "@layouts/Default.astro";
import "../../styles/resources.css";
---

<Layout
  title="Resources"
  pageTitle="Resources"
  description="Tech clubs, how-to guides, and FAQs for ACM at William & Mary."
>
  <main class="resources">
    <header class="hero">
      <h1>Resources</h1>
      <p>Quick links for tech clubs, setup guides, and ACM basics.</p>
    </header>

    <!-- 1) tech clubs -->
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="clubs">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2 id="clubs">Tech clubs at William &amp; Mary</h2>
        <p>Explore nearby communities (and collaborators) across campus.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid">
        <a class="card" href="https://wmswc.github.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <div class="card-top">
            <h3>Society of Women in Computing</h3>
            <span class="pill">networking</span>
          </div>
          <p>Community and mentorship supporting women and allies in computing.</p>
        </a>

        <a
          class="card"
          href="https://gdg.community.dev/gdg-on-campus-william-mary-williamsburg-united-states/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          <div class="card-top">
            <h3>GDG on Campus (Developer Student Club)</h3>
            <span class="pill">build</span>
          </div>
          <p>Build apps/sites/scripts and support campus groups and nonprofits.</p>
        </a>

        <a class="card" href="https://cybersecurity.wm.edu/tribe-cyber/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <div class="card-top">
            <h3>Tribe Cyber</h3>
            <span class="pill">security</span>
          </div>
          <p>Cybersecurity learning, competition, and community at W&amp;M.</p>
        </a>

        <a class="card" href="https://aiclubwm.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <div class="card-top">
            <h3>AI Club</h3>
            <span class="pill">ai</span>
          </div>
          <p>Learn AI fundamentals, build projects, and explore research opportunities.</p>
        </a>
        
        <a class="card" href="https://tribelink.wm.edu/organization/robotics" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <div class="card-top">
            <h3>Robotics Club</h3>
            <span class="pill">build</span>
          </div>
          <p>Collaborative, project-based club for building robots and hands-on engineering.</p>
        </a>

        <a
          class="card"
          href="https://www.wm.edu/student-life/clubs-organizations/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          <div class="card-top">
            <h3>Find more clubs</h3>
            <span class="pill">directory</span>
          </div>
          <p>Browse W&amp;M’s club directory if you’re looking for something specific.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 2) how-to pages -->
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="howto">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2 id="howto">How-to guides</h2>
        <p>Common setup and access links for CS resources.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="list">
        <a
          class="row"
          href="https://support.cs.wm.edu/index.php/faq-support-articles/ssh-keys/ssh-into-a-machine"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          <div class="row-main">
            <h3>How to SSH into a CS machine</h3>
            <p>Official CS Support guide for connecting to department machines.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>

        <a class="row" href="https://www.cs.wm.edu/~tadavis/remoteaccess.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <div class="row-main">
            <h3>Remote access for CS accounts</h3>
            <p>Helpful notes on SSH and remote login examples.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>

        <a class="row" href="https://accounts.cs.wm.edu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <div class="row-main">
            <h3>Create a CS account</h3>
            <p>Request your CS department account (if you don’t have one yet).</p>
          </div>
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>

        <a class="row" href="https://support.cs.wm.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <div class="row-main">
            <h3>CS Support tutorials</h3>
            <p>Knowledgebase, machine specs, and guides from CS Support.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>

        <a class="row" href="https://www.wm.edu/offices/it/services/researchcomputing/acctreq/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <div class="row-main">
            <h3>Request an HPC account</h3>
            <p>For research computing (HPC/Sciclone) access via W&amp;M IT.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 3) faq -->
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="faq">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2 id="faq">ACM @ W&amp;M FAQ</h2>
        <p>Answers to the most common questions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq">
        <details class="qa">
          <summary>Do I need to be a CS major to join?</summary>
          <div class="answer">
            <p>No. Anyone can join. We welcome all majors and experience levels.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="qa">
          <summary>Where are meetings?</summary>
          <div class="answer">
            <p>Thursdays at <strong>7:00 PM</strong> in <strong>ISC 2280</strong>.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="qa">
          <summary>When are office hours?</summary>
          <div class="answer">
            <p>
              Monday–Friday in <strong>ISC 2394</strong>:
              <br />
              <strong>9–11 AM</strong>, <strong>3–5 PM</strong>, <strong>6–7 PM</strong>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="qa">
          <summary>How do I get updates?</summary>
          <div class="answer">
            <p>
              Use the <a href="/connect">Connect</a> page to join Discord/GroupMe and follow socials.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="qa">
          <summary>What kinds of events does ACM run?</summary>
          <div class="answer">
            <p>Workshops, speaker talks, project team meetups, and social events.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="qa">
          <summary>Can I suggest an event or give a workshop?</summary>
          <div class="answer">
            <p>
              Yes. Message an officer on Discord or GroupMe.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
